text: @Lord Fendleberry: Episode I: Pod Racer also had real music. Unfortunately, both games’ music were heavily compressed and shortened, but I liked them still far more than say the digital score in Rogue Squadron. Factor 5 was praised for their music technology for the N64 and later Game Cube games, but I wasn’t impressed with their synthy soundtracks—especially the odd combined real John Williams OST with synthetic parts in the Rogue Leader games. The only other games I can think of that had (heavily compressed) real music were WipeOut 64 (with loading times as a result) and Killer Instinct Gold.
